The creatively written science fiction novel, "Divergent" is must read for anyone looking to spice up their leisurely reading. Author Veronica Roth paints a world where people are divided into five factions. The factions are Candor, Erudite, Abnegation, Amity, and Dauntless. Each of the factions believe in different moral codes that one should follow. For example, the people of Candor always tell the truth, no matter how harsh it may be. In this fictional society, once children reach adulthood, they must chose whether to stay with their family in the faction they grow up in, or switch to a different one. Once the choice is made, there is no looking back. <span style="line-height: 1.5">The main character, Beatrice Prior, must make the most important decision of her life. Will she stay with her family in Abnegation, or leave to explore a new life in a different faction? Her choices have strong </span>repercussions, and all that she loves is hanging on a thin thread. <span style="line-height: 1.5"> </span>

"Divergent" may be fiction, but it challenges real life issues. This is a book not easily forgotten.

