This past Saturday, the Friends Academy Quakers lost in a shootout against Island Trees. A shout out has to go out to Senior, Cyrus Holder, for scoring 5 touchdowns (4 receiving and 1 kickoff) and tallying more than 300 total all purpose yards. He leads all of Long Island in receiving touchdowns with 7. Junior Quarterback, Corey Goldglit is 3<sup>rd</sup> on Long Island in Passing Touchdowns with 9.

